---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="About Robert Slowinski — amateur photographer based in Boulder, Colorado">

  <div class="about-wrap">

    <div class="about-photos">
      <img src="/images/about/self.jpg" alt="Robert Slowinski" />
    </div>

    <div class="about-bio">
      <h1>Robert Slowinski</h1>
      <p class="location">Boulder, Colorado</p>

      <p>
        Welcome! I'm an amateur photographer based in Boulder, Colorado. With my other time,
        I'm also a wannabe entrepreneur, samba musician, road biker, backyard astronomer,
        upright bassist, home remodeling contractor and salsa dancer as well as a professional
        green building engineer.
      </p>

      <p>
        I dove into photography right around the year 2000, just before being bitten by the
        international travel bug. I started with a film SLR, but quickly moved up to the world's
        first 'affordable' consumer digital SLR (the Nikon D70). While my photography equipment
        (and my bicycle) has changed a bit over the years, a lot of these photos were shot on
        what I'm currently using — a Micro 4/3rds Olympus OM-D E-M5 and various lenses.
        Some of these photos were shot with that very first film SLR, as well as various phone
        cameras and a few others in between.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site is a reincarnation of my previous travel and photography website, which had
        been shuttered since about 2008. Enjoy!
      </p>

      <div class="contact">
        Print &amp; licensing inquiries: <a href="mailto:rfslowphoto@gmail.com">rfslowphoto@gmail.com</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</Base>
